<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE - 3200, 4100, 4200, 4300, 4400, 7300, 7400, 7500, 7600, 8500, 8600
        Models Built After 05/19/2003 - LIGHT SYSTEMS - DOME AND MAP LIGHTS - DOOR SWITCH INPUTS INTO ESC
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc id="x08260402" svcproctype="troubleshoot" graphiccount="1">
        <title>DOOR SWITCH INPUTS INTO ESC</title>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Fault Detection Management</title>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>The testing method for troubleshooting the electrical systems portrayed in this manual is a
                        basic voltage test. An alternative method of checking for voltage drops within a given circuit
                        may be a quicker method of identifying an exact problem.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <para>Refer to
                <hotlnk xrefid="f0826018">Door Switch Circuits to ESC</hotlnk>.
            </para>
            <para>Several options are available for door switches. Options range from one switch on the drivers door to
                switches on every door.
            </para>
            <para>A problem in the door switch circuit(s) will prevent the lights from operating when one or both doors
                are opened. A problem in the door switch circuits could be attributed to a defective switch, a problem
                in the ESC, a short circuit or an open circuit.
            </para>
            <figure id="f0826018" figsize="pg-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg08/g0826032.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="448px"/>
                <caption>Door Switch Circuits to ESC (Connectors Viewed From Mating End) - Always Refer To Circuit
                    Diagram Book For Latest Circuit Information
                </caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>(1600) 36-WAY ESC CONNECTOR
                        <callout2>LOCATED ON CAB SIDE OF ESC</callout2>
                    </callout1>
                    <callout1>(2000) ROOF CONNECTOR
                        <callout2>LOCATED NEAR DRIVER SIDE A PILLAR</callout2>
                    </callout1>
                    <callout1>(2111) RIGHT DOOR DOME SWITCH CONNECTOR
                        <callout2>LOCATED IN PASSENGER SIDE B PILLAR</callout2>
                    </callout1>
                    <callout1>(2112) LEFT DOOR DOME SWITCH CONNECTOR
                        <callout2>LOCATED IN DRIVER SIDE B PILLAR</callout2>
                    </callout1>
                    <callout1>(2113) RIGHT CREW DOOR DOME SWITCH CONNECTOR
                        <callout2>LOCATED IN PASSENGER SIDE C PILLAR (CREW CAB ONLY)</callout2>
                    </callout1>
                    <callout1>(2114) LEFT CREW DOOR DOME SWITCH CONNECTOR
                        <callout2>LOCATED IN DRIVER SIDE C PILLAR (CREW CAB ONLY)</callout2>
                    </callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <table id="t0826009" tblwidth="pg-wide" numbered="no" view="reveal">
                <title>Door Switch Circuit Tests</title>
                <tgroup cols="6">
                    <colspec colname="1" colwidth="1.56in"/>
                    <colspec colname="2" colwidth="0.92in"/>
                    <colspec colname="3" colwidth="0.98in"/>
                    <colspec colname="4" colwidth="0.89in"/>
                    <colspec colname="5" colwidth="0.87in"/>
                    <colspec colname="6" colwidth="0.91in"/>
                    <spanspec namest="3" nameend="6" spanname="SPAN2"/>
                    <spanspec namest="4" nameend="6" spanname="S4T6"/>
                    <spanspec namest="1" nameend="6" spanname="S1T6"/>
                    <spanspec namest="2" nameend="3" spanname="S2T3"/>
                    <tbody>
                        <row>
                            <entry colspan="6" spanname="S1T6" align="center">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">FAULTS</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry colspan="6" spanname="S1T6" align="center">
                                <para>There are no diagnostic trouble codes associated with door switch circuits.</para>
                                <note>
                                    <para>Always use breakout box ZTSE 4477 to take measurements on ESC connectors.
                                    </para>
                                </note>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry colname="1">
                                <para>Test Points</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colspan="2" spanname="S2T3">
                                <para>Spec.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colspan="3" spanname="S4T6" align="center">
                                <para>Comments</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry colname="1" align="center">
                                <para>Harness connector cavity A to ground.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colspan="2" spanname="S2T3">
                                <para>12 &#177; 1.5 volts with ignition on, 5 &#177; .5 with ignition off.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colspan="3" spanname="S4T6" align="center">
                                <para>If voltage is missing, check for open in circuits D63A or A63A. Also check for
                                    short in circuits D63A, A63A or circuits to other door switches.
                                </para>
                                <para>Also insure proper voltage out of ESC.</para>
                                <para>
                                    <hotlnk document="s082504_X0825310A.xml" xrefid="x0825310a">Refer to ESC Replacement
                                        in this manual.
                                        <xref refid="x0825310a"/>
                                    </hotlnk>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry colname="1" align="center">
                                <para>Harness connector cavity B to ground.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colspan="2" spanname="S2T3" align="center">
                                <para>&#60;.3 volts</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colspan="3" spanname="S4T6" align="center">
                                <para>Zero volt reference level signal.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry colname="1" align="center">
                                <para>Harness connector cavity A to cavity B.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colspan="2" spanname="S2T3" align="center">
                                <para>12 &#177; 1.5 volts with ignition off. 5 &#177; .5 with ignition off.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colspan="3" spanname="S4T6" align="center">
                                <para>If voltage is missing, check for open in circuits between ESC connector (1600)
                                    cavity D and dome switch connector cavity B. A missing zero volt reference level
                                    from the ESC will cause several other features to be inoperative.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry colspan="6" spanname="S1T6" align="center">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="BOLD">Door Switch (2112) Resistance Checks</emph>
                                </para>
                                <para>Check at door switch.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry colname="1" align="center">
                                <para>Resistance between door switch connector pins A and B.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colspan="2" spanname="S2T3" align="center">
                                <para>&#60;1 ohm with door open. >50K ohms with piece of steel in front of switch.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colspan="3" spanname="S4T6" align="center">
                                <para>If resistance is incorrect replace defective switch.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry colspan="6" spanname="S1T6" align="center">
                                <para>If the door switch and door switch circuits check good proceed to the
                                    <hotlnk document="s082504_X08260403.xml" xrefid="x08260403">dome light circuit
                                        checks
                                        <xref refid="x08260403"/>
                                    </hotlnk>
                                    .
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                    </tbody>
                </tgroup>
            </table>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Extended Description</title>
            <para>Refer to
                <hotlnk xrefid="f0826018">Door Switch Circuits to ESC</hotlnk>.
            </para>
            <para>A proximity switch is used for the door switch(es). When steel passes in front of the switch it will
                open. When the door is opened the switch will close.
            </para>
            <para>The ESC monitors the voltage at ESC connector (1600). When a door switch closes, a zero volt reference
                signal from the ESC will be applied through the door switch back to the ESC. This will cause the voltage
                to drop and the ESC will turn the dome light(s) on.
            </para>
        </svcsubproc>
    </svcproc>
